
[1]loin

   LOIN, n. [L. clumis.]

   The loins are the space on each side of the vertebrae, between the
   lowest of the false ribs and the upper portion of the os ilium or
   haunch bone, or the lateral portions of the lumbar region; called also
   the reins.
